01:02:16.916 --> 01:02:19.685 line:90% position:50% align:center
One part of the world
where the disciple-making work

01:02:19.685 --> 01:02:22.789 line:90% position:50% align:center
has been thriving
for well over 100 years

01:02:22.789 --> 01:02:25.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
is Australia, our destination

01:02:25.491 --> 01:02:27.827 line:90% position:50% align:center
in this month’s video postcard.

01:02:29.195 --> 01:02:31.764 line:90% position:50% align:center
Australia is a vast island continent

01:02:31.764 --> 01:02:34.467 line:90% position:50% align:center
four times larger
than the largest island in the world.

01:02:35.701 --> 01:02:38.738 line:90% position:50% align:center
Situated between the Indian
and Pacific oceans,

01:02:38.738 --> 01:02:42.141 line:90% position:50% align:center
Australia is a land of dramatic contrasts.

01:02:42.141 --> 01:02:46.012 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s the second driest continent
after Antarctica,

01:02:46.012 --> 01:02:48.147 line:90% position:50% align:center
with vast deserts.

01:02:48.147 --> 01:02:51.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yet, some of its mountain ranges
receive enough snow

01:02:51.284 --> 01:02:54.454 line:90% position:50% align:center
to have earned the name the Australian Alps!

01:02:55.321 --> 01:02:58.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
Off the coast of Queensland in the northeast,

01:02:58.491 --> 01:03:00.960 line:90% position:50% align:center
you’ll find the Great Barrier Reef,

01:03:00.960 --> 01:03:04.430 line:90% position:50% align:center
which is the largest coral reef system
on earth!

01:03:04.430 --> 01:03:06.833 line:90% position:50% align:center
Whether you’re traveling
in Australia’s dusty outback

01:03:06.833 --> 01:03:09.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
or along the coast,

01:03:09.068 --> 01:03:11.237 line:90% position:50% align:center
you’ll likely see many kangaroos.

01:03:11.237 --> 01:03:13.739 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s not surprising because there are

01:03:13.739 --> 01:03:17.243 line:90% position:50% align:center
many more kangaroos in Australia
than there are people.

01:03:17.243 --> 01:03:20.546 line:90% position:50% align:center
Kangaroos are native to Australia,
as are many other animals,

01:03:20.546 --> 01:03:22.648 line:90% position:50% align:center
including the koala,

01:03:22.648 --> 01:03:24.617 line:90% position:50% align:center
wombat,

01:03:24.617 --> 01:03:26.519 line:90% position:50% align:center
possum,

01:03:26.519 --> 01:03:28.621 line:90% position:50% align:center
emu,

01:03:29.255 --> 01:03:31.257 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the unique duck-billed platypus.

01:03:32.492 --> 01:03:34.594 line:90% position:50% align:center
Seeds of truth reached Australia

01:03:34.594 --> 01:03:37.463 line:90% position:50% align:center
as far back as 1884.

01:03:37.463 --> 01:03:40.867 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Australia branch was established in 1904,

01:03:40.867 --> 01:03:43.469 line:90% position:50% align:center
making it one of the oldest branches
in the world.

01:03:43.469 --> 01:03:46.906 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today it’s called the Australasia branch

01:03:46.906 --> 01:03:48.908 line:90% position:50% align:center
and oversees the preaching

01:03:48.908 --> 01:03:50.910 line:90% position:50% align:center
not just in Australia and New Zealand

01:03:50.910 --> 01:03:53.412 line:90% position:50% align:center
but in many islands of the South Pacific.

01:03:54.413 --> 01:03:56.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the early days,

01:03:56.082 --> 01:03:58.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
brothers covered the vast Australian territory

01:03:58.284 --> 01:04:02.021 line:90% position:50% align:center
traveling by bicycle, truck, cart,

01:04:02.021 --> 01:04:04.023 line:90% position:50% align:center
and even camel.

01:04:05.858 --> 01:04:10.830 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today, more than 70,400 publishers
and 7,500 pioneers

01:04:10.830 --> 01:04:13.900 line:90% position:50% align:center
are preaching
in almost 40 different languages.

01:04:13.900 --> 01:04:16.269 line:90% position:50% align:center
A special effort is made to reach

01:04:16.269 --> 01:04:18.905 line:90% position:50% align:center
Australia’s native Aboriginal people.

01:04:18.905 --> 01:04:20.907 line:90% position:50% align:center
To assist those hungering for the truth,

01:04:20.907 --> 01:04:25.077 line:90% position:50% align:center
literature has been translated
into some of the indigenous languages.

01:04:26.712 --> 01:04:29.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our Australian brothers and sisters
have also found success

01:04:29.682 --> 01:04:34.053 line:90% position:50% align:center
preaching on passenger trains
and at railway stations.

01:04:34.053 --> 01:04:36.422 line:10% position:50% align:center
This is the Broken Hill Station,

01:04:36.422 --> 01:04:39.292 line:10% position:50% align:center
a stop on the <i>Indian Pacific</i>  route,

01:04:39.292 --> 01:04:42.128 line:10% position:50% align:center
which runs more than 4,300 kilometers,

01:04:42.128 --> 01:04:45.965 line:10% position:50% align:center
or about 2,700 miles, from Sydney to Perth.

01:04:45.965 --> 01:04:47.667 line:10% position:50% align:center
Many have learned the truth

01:04:47.667 --> 01:04:49.168 line:10% position:50% align:center
as a result of the preaching

01:04:49.168 --> 01:04:51.170 line:10% position:50% align:center
along this train line.

01:04:51.170 --> 01:04:54.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
Most of Australia’s nearly
26 million inhabitants

01:04:54.840 --> 01:04:57.677 line:90% position:50% align:center
live in cities and towns
not far from the coast.

01:04:57.677 --> 01:04:59.679 line:90% position:50% align:center
One of those towns is Nowra,

01:04:59.679 --> 01:05:02.448 line:90% position:50% align:center
home of the Nowra-West Congregation.

01:05:03.282 --> 01:05:05.151 line:90% position:50% align:center
With a little help from Zoom,

01:05:05.151 --> 01:05:06.786 line:90% position:50% align:center
the 80 brothers and sisters

01:05:06.786 --> 01:05:08.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the Nowra-West Congregation

01:05:08.988 --> 01:05:11.090 line:90% position:50% align:center
send you their warmest love.

01:05:12.224 --> 01:05:15.027 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the world headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

01:05:15.027 --> 01:05:17.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
this is JW Broadcasting.

